Language name: KPELLE
Language number: 4103
Alternate names: 
Classification: Niger-Kordofanian, Mande
Comments: Voiced plosives and fricatives can be 
morphophonemically derived (in initial position following 
a low-toned nasal, which deletes).  Kpelle has three 
surface level tones.

Sources: 

Hyman, L.M. 1973. Notes on the history of Southwestern 
Mande. Studies in African Linguistics 4: 183-96.

Welmers, W.E. 1962. The phonology of Kpelle. Journal of 
African Languages 1: 69-93.

Welmers, W.E. 1973. African Language Structures. 
University of California Press, Berkeley.